# MoneyBin - Mortgage Plan Application

## Overview
The MoneyBin Mortgage Plan Application is a web-based calculator designed to help users determine their monthly payments for a mortgage based on loan amount, interest rate, and repayment period. Users can enter their loan details to see how much they need to pay each month.

## Features
- Calculate monthly mortgage payments
- Input fields for loan amount, interest rate, and loan period
- Clear and user-friendly web interface
- Reads from a text file prospect.txt and base on the values from the file is counting the monthly payment for 3 users and the prints the results in the console in this form:
  #CustomerName wants to borrow X € for a period of Z years and pay E € each month

## Getting Started with Docker

### Prerequisites
- Docker installed on your system

### Building the Docker Image
To build the Docker image for the application, navigate to the project root directory and run:
docker build -t myapp:latest .


### Running the Application
Run the application using:
docker run -p 8080:8080 myapp:latest

Access the application by navigating to `http://localhost:8080` in your web browser.


## Accessing the Application

The application is hosted on AWS and can be accessed through the following URL:

[http://myapp-env.eba-2uin4aat.eu-west-1.elasticbeanstalk.com/web/view](http://myapp-env.eba-2uin4aat.eu-west-1.elasticbeanstalk.com/web/view)

## Stopping the Application
To stop the application, press CTRL+C if running in the foreground. Alternatively, use `docker ps` to find the container ID and stop it with `docker stop <container_id>`.

